@Terablast - Actually, Super Smash Bros. Brawl has it written as "Bramble Blast" but the same remix from Brawl that is used in Super Smash Bros. for Wii U / Nintendo 3DS was renamed to "Stickerbush Symphony". And Stickerbush Symphony is also the song title in the official DKC2 soundtrack. (Smash 4 helped us confirm the official sound title).

@Comp's Computer Repair - The only time where I noticed "Sitckerbrush Symphony" was in the GBA Music Player cheat mode in the GBA version. And I think the SNES sound test calls it "Bramble".

But now for my main question that's been bugging me for a long time: "Mine" (SNES sound test), "Mining Melancholy" (that most fans call it), or "Kannon's Klaim" (GBA Music Player, sharing the same name as level)? Too bad that song was never added on the official soundtrack (but I think it was on a bootleg soundtrack as "Mining Melancholy", where it started).

